missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md:11:The refined chain separates them and asks a narrower question first: can any scale-appropriate local geometric observable on intense-vorticity regions control the full vortex-stretching mechanism, including nonlocal exterior contributions? If not, the right output is a rigorous fragility memo, not a recycled conditional criterion.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:13:**Judgment: Valid**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:15:This is the central criticism. The original Step 1 let the chain choose among heterogeneous bottlenecks and heterogeneous gain currencies before committing to the exact estimate or contradiction point where the gain was supposed to matter. That invites retrofitting. The refined chain therefore requires, at the start, one theorem-level target inequality or contradiction point, one admissible solution framework, one representation, and one gain currency measured inside that target.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:19:**Judgment: Valid**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:21:The attacker is right that a ledger of helicity signs, resonance classes, and Leray-symbol identities is cheap unless it is tied to the sign, size, or summability of a specific term in a specific estimate. The original chain also left "Tao-sensitive" too informal. The refined chain keeps the ledger but makes it operational: each promoted feature must be attached to the chosen estimate and assigned a maximal plausible quantitative effect before full reconstruction.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:25:**Judgment: Valid**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:27:Difference from an averaged model is not evidence of theorem relevance by itself. The original chain treated this distinction as more probative than it really is. The refined chain demotes it to a secondary discriminator: useful only after the feature has already shown potential leverage on the fixed bottleneck term under a precisely stated comparison class.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:31:**Judgment: Valid**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:33:This lands cleanly. Once a mechanism is promoted, the chain should already be able to write the candidate inequality, transfer estimate, or contradiction line where the mechanism enters. Otherwise the route has not crossed from interpretation to proof pressure. The refined chain now requires an explicit candidate inequality in Step 3.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:37:**Judgment: Partially Valid**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:43:**Judgment: Valid**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:45:Correct. In this subject the best-looking same-helicity or near-resonant sectors are often exactly where full-equation relevance is weakest. The refined chain therefore requires any restricted interaction class to come with a quantified share of the relevant transfer or shell sum. Otherwise the branch dies as a regime artifact.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:49:**Judgment: Valid**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:51:This is the strongest criticism and the core of the refined chain. "Charge the full cost" was directionally right but too rhetorical. The revised version requires an explicit reconstruction ledger that includes shell summation, angular multiplicity, non-favorable triads, and localization or commutator losses when the theorem target needs them.
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:55:**Judgment: Valid**
missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:57:By the time the chain reaches the last stage, any surviving mechanism should already look theorem-shaped. The attacker is also right about asymmetry: a sharp obstruction memo is more plausible than a positive regularity mechanism. The refined chain keeps both branches, but it now treats obstruction extraction as the default likely success mode.
